description:
From humorously twisted Future Shocks to the dystopian escapades of Judge Dredd, 2000 AD has inspired generations of readers and has spawned some of the greatest talents in the comics industry.

To celebrate the creative droids behind the Galaxy‚Äôs Greatest Comic, a selection of writers and artists from across 2000 AD‚Äôs forty-year history were asked to choose their favourite one-off story by a fellow creator and explain why they chose it. The result is this incredible anthology featuring work by Alan Grant, Kevin O‚ÄôNeill, Rob Williams, Brian Bolland, Chris Weston and Steve Dillon selected by creators such as founding editor Pat Mills, celebrated artist Jock and recent newcomer Tom Foster.

Stories include:

  • Tharg and the Intruder
  • Meat
  • The Sweet Taste of Justice
  • Mutie's Luck
  • The Forever Crimes
  • Shok!
  • Krong
  • The Heart is a Lonely Klegg Hunter
  • The Strange Case of the Wyndham Demon
  • The Sword Sinister
  • Beyond The Wall
  • The Runner
  • A Close Encounter of the Fatal Kind!

description:
Three teenagers, Talinn, Evrane, and the very young Corky, live in a small village in the vast Kingdom of Angor. As members of the lowest caste, their future is all mapped out; they have to till the soil and raise livestock alongside their parents. However, all three dream of chivalry, adventure, and freedom. But if they want to be masters of their own destiny, they have to leave the City, no matter the cost.

After Talinn witnesses a murderous confrontation between two knights, they lay hands on a necklace with magical properties they can't imagine. And event that is the first step on their long and epic journey...
name: Runaway

description:
The most groundbreaking event in Aspen Comics' history collected!!! For over thirteen years, devoted Aspen Comics fans clamored for something special...something unique...something...UNIMAGINABLE! Aspen Comics answered the call for loyal fans and new readers alike with ASPEN UNIVERSE: REVELATIONS. Legendary creator Michael Turner's two greatest creations, FATHOM and SOULFIRE, united for the first time as one in this crossover story so massive in scope, it forged a BRAND NEW ASPEN UNIVERSE in the process! A magical being of unimaginable might has destroyed the world as they knew it, and it remains up to Soulfire‚Äôs magical bearer of the light, Malikai, along with Fathom‚Äôs preeminent heroine, Aspen Matthews, to try and restore order and peace to a world decimated by the malevolent power of dark magic!

Note: The digital edition (2/8/2017) for this volume was released before the print edition.
name: Vol. 1

description: It's the end of the world and few are worthy of passage to heaven, not even the Pope. God leaves behind Saint Michael, to act as a guardian for the humans. He fails, and is held captive by Luicfer. God enlists the aide of the Pope to rescue Michael, and leaves his son, Jesus H Christ to assist him in his quest. This volume is presented in color.

description: Picking up right where volume one left off, this collection paves the way for all future Battle Pope stories. Featuring the downfall of HellCorp and Pope's rise to local celebrity status, plus as many fights, guns, jokes, chicks and violence as you can fit in a 120-page trade paperback. This one has it all.

description: Picking up right were Volume 2 left off, this edition follows Pope through three love affairs and the sometimes deadly ramifications of them all. Jesus Vs. Santa! Pope makes time with the Virgin Mary! This one has it all.

description: Comic Shop News is comics' weekly newsletter. Each issue is full-color, 8-12 pages in length, and features CSNsider, news, and interviews. CSN has a complete monthly checklist (complete with PREVIEWS order numbers), plus exclusive CSN Hot Picks, 'Fab Firsts,' and a monthly checklist of all the first issues for the month!

Rebellious Youth, Part Two: Close Calls

Things come to a head as the Commander races to save his adopted daughter.

description:
In 1940, small time crook Ned Turpin claimed to be the descendant of the infamous highwayman, Dick Turpin. He, with his partner in crime, Bert Bloomer, had no intention of involving himself in the war‚Ä¶ or at least until he was caught robbing notorious East London gangsters, the Bailey brothers.

Shipped off to France to avoid the Baileys and time behind bars, Ned and Bert found themselves on the front line in a war they wanted no part of. The advancing Germans had heard many cries on the battlefields but now they would hear the screams of‚Ä¶ Achtung, we surrender!

Note: The digital edition (2/8/2017) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Achtung, We Surrender

description:
The Foreign Legion breeds tough men. Sergeant Steve Millar was tough ‚Äì he needed to be.

He was stranded in the desert with a fortune of gold. He knew he would be attacked by Germans, Italians and marauding Arabs. And for company he had four legionnaires ‚Äì killers all, with the smell of gold in their nostrils.

Note: The digital edition (2/8/2017) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Legion of the Lost

description:
Seaman Andy Walker had been a loner all his life. From his beginnings at the orphanage to his posting in the Royal Navy, Andy struggled to be accepted‚Ä¶

But Andy‚Äôs isolation worsened when he was captured and put in a Japanese prisoner of war camp. Once his jailers learnt he could speak their language, he was singled out and, from his fellow prisoners‚Äô perspective, given special treatment.

It would take everything Andy had to prove he was no traitor, no Japanese pet‚Ä¶ to prove that he was one of them. That he was a Barbed Wire Battler!

Note: The digital edition (2/8/2017) for this issue was released before the print edition.
name: Barbed Wire Battlers

description:
The Bristol Beaufighter packed an awesome punch with its arsenal of machine guns and cannons. Turned against an enemy, it was a lethal weapon of war.

But one Beaufighter pilot, Andy Shaw, knew to his cost that it could be just as deadly against a friendly target hit by mistake‚Ä¶

Note: The digital edition (2/8/2017) for this issue was released before the print edition.

description: With Doctor Strange working on being more grounded and the Punisher trying to adjust to magic, this mismatched pair has their work cut out for them with a mobster family transformed into demons!

description:
The confrontation between Fall, the White Elf, and Lha'saa, the Black Elf Necromancer...

Lha'saa and her legions of the dead spread desolation and chaos everywhere they go. No lord, no army, no wall seems to be able to stop the Black Elf Necromancer... Until Fall and his dragon stand in her way. It is time for the oldest and strongest creatures of the world to confront each other.

The battlefield awaits them: who will die, the White or the Black Elf?
name: Happily, The Warrior Dies

description: Things are finally looking up for Molly. Sarahh hooks her up with a sweet job at the trendy website, TheSauce, as an in-house artist. But being a professional artist isn't easy, and it's even more confusing when your boss is throwing startup clich√©s at you. With the brogrammers at work telling her she's not good enough, Molly's head is spinning. Luckily, this catsitter's got a few trick in her bag, Specifically, a cat.

volume.name: Finding Molly: An Adventure In Catsitting

description: Things at work haven't been going well for Molly and to make things worse she's just met Lorona, Mateo's new, silver-haired girlfriend. Can Molly find a way to successfully launch her art career and land the man of her dreams? Only her trusty (?) cats can help her now!

volume.name: Finding Molly: An Adventure In Catsitting

WX's gleeful torture of Subject K is interrupted. Doc Layne and Leo struggle to understand the tattooing of Spez's brain by looking to the past. Doctor Vernon goes on a limb, putting her position at risk.

description: Rayven is still haunted by the nightmares of her past when she discovers a secret tape that her father left behind. The confession on the tape leads her back to America on the hunt for a killer who may still be on the hunt for her.

description: Dispatched to America in the early '60s, the golden age of illustrative reportage, Ronald Searle spent several years covering everything‚Äïin the form of drawings in his trademark satirical and virtuosic style‚Äïfrom sports to politics, for magazines such as The Saturday Evening Post and TV Guide. Topics included Palm Springs, Las Vegas, the Presidential contest between John F. Kennedy and Richard Nixon‚Äïas seen through the eyes of a caustic Englishman.

description: Quick Draw McGraw may be the high-falutin‚Äôest, fastest-shootin‚Äôest lawman on the lone prairie, but he needs help from Scooby and the gang when faced with that rustlin‚Äô wraith, the Fastest Ghost in the West!
name: Go West, You Meddling Kids Part 1

description: The team‚Äôs split up as Taipuitea and Katsuko navigate the dangerous alleyways of Chinatown on their way to Qiulong‚Äôs Teahouse. The savage Danny Yuda and calculating Mr. Song work feverishly to corner their prey and recover the Tanto octopus. Meanwhile Hans and the rest of the crew arrive at Hashima Island and find themselves as reluctant houseguests of the treacherous Fox.

Vader's down - but not out! When a rebel encounter sends the Sith Lord crashing onto a nearby planet, two of the biggest titles in comics collide in the first crossover of the new Marvel age of Star Wars! Will the heroes of the Alliance seize this opportunity to put an end to one of their greatest enemies - or will they be made to feel the full power of the dark side? Darth Vader has been secretly pursuing his own agenda, but now the time has come for the end of games. He will either find favor in the eyes of the Emperor, or his schemes will prove his undoing! The imperial march of Darth Vader hits in full stride! Collecting STAR WARS: VADER DOWN #1, STAR WARS (2015) #13-14, and DARTH VADER #13-25 and ANNUAL #1.

The United States, nowadays. When William Peter Stahl, a famous politician, announces his aim to participate in the presidential race, four childhood friends recall their promise... For these four know this man... They are the only ones who know the horrors that he committed more than thirty years ago.

Getting in touch with each other, they go back to where it all started, in order to stop this man who is the embodiment of evil... They have to revive their old secret superhero group - The Vigilantes!

After the fiasco of Pitsgreen, Daryl, Zack, Curtis, and Jesse have to keep a low profile... While they prepare their final counterattack ‚Äì The Vigilantes return in force to stop the serial killer once and for all. But will their superpowers be enough?

END OF THE STORY.
